## Impact Radius

### Single Child Project

- Read only the affected child skill.
- Keep writes inside that child project path by default.
- If the change requires contracts, shared code, or deployment config, escalate to cross-project work.

### Contract Changes

- Includes API definitions, OpenAPI/Swagger, proto, request/response types, error codes, events, messages, generation inputs, and SDKs.
- Update the contract source first, then generated artifacts or adapters.
- Read producer and consumer child skills together.
- Verify fields, types, error codes, defaults, compatibility, and tests on both sides.

### Shared Code Changes

- Includes public types, utilities, shared components, common config, and reused libraries.
- Stabilize public APIs or function signatures before updating consumers.
- Check importers, build targets, and packaged artifacts.
- If the shared change is breaking, update every consumer in the same change set.

### Infrastructure Changes

- Includes Dockerfiles, Compose, Kubernetes, Helm, Terraform, Nginx, gateways, middleware, environment variables, CI, and release scripts.
- Identify runtime-affected child projects before reading skills.
- Check ports, path prefixes, health checks, environment variable names, image build args, startup commands, and release order.

## Change Order

{{if .HasChangeOrder}}
{{range $i, $step := .ChangeOrder}}
{{add $i 1}}. {{$step}}
{{end}}
{{else}}
1. List affected paths and child projects.
2. Read the workspace overview to confirm child skill paths.
3. If contracts or shared interfaces are involved, update the contract source, schema, public types, or shared signatures first.
4. Update producer implementation and tests.
5. Update consumer calls, generated code, adapters, and tests.
6. Update infrastructure, environment variables, gateway rules, middleware, or CI.
7. Verify consistency across generated artifacts, interface shapes, error codes, config keys, build commands, and test scope.
{{end}}

## Load Multiple Skills When

- The changed path is not owned by exactly one child project.
- The change affects APIs, types, schemas, error codes, events, messages, or generation inputs.
- The change touches shared libraries, utilities, components, or common config.
- The change touches deployment, gateway, middleware, CI, environment variables, or release scripts.
- The change touches root scripts, workspace-level package/go work/build config, or batch commands.
{{if .HasContracts}}
- A configured contract path changes; read related producer, consumer, middleware, or SDK child skills together.
{{end}}
{{if .HasShared}}
- A configured shared path changes; read every child skill that imports, packages, or generates the shared code.
{{end}}
{{if .HasInfra}}
- A configured infrastructure path changes; read child skills affected by deployment, config, gateway, or middleware rules.
{{end}}
{{if .HasLoadMultipleWhen}}
{{range .LoadMultipleWhen}}
