{{end}}
{{end}}

## Parallel Agent Constraints

- Safe to parallelize: non-overlapping child-project internals where each agent writes only its assigned child project path.
- Do not parallelize: the same contract file, shared file, infrastructure file, root config, or workspace-level script.
- Before parallel work, define each agent's read/write boundary and affected child projects.
- Consumer projects must not proceed in parallel until the contract or shared interface is stable.
- Before merging parallel results, verify interface shapes, error codes, environment variables, generated artifacts, build commands, and tests together.
